news.title: Construction equipment sales rise 5% to 28,902 units in Q1 FY25: ICEMA
news.para: ​As per the data released by the Indian Construction Equipment Manufacturers' Association (ICEMA), the construction equipment (CE) industry had sold 27,577 units in the same period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Two years on, Gurugram civic body takes over upkeep of Mayfield Gardens
news.para: In a grievance committee meeting held on June 27, CM Nayab Singh Saini directed MCG to take over the colony and attach the developer's properties if it didn't pay development charges.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh CM inaugurates Swamitva Yojana, distributes property cards to beneficiaries
news.para: The chief minister distributed property cards to 10 families each from 11 tehsils. In the first phase, more than 4,230 families across 190 villages would receive their property cards, a statement issued here said.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA puts 400 projects in 'abeyance'
news.para: UP-RERA found that promoters of about 400 projects had not uploaded the land records or maps or both of the projects on RERA portal. It was also seen that the promoters of 160 of these projects have not uploaded both the map and land record.

news.title: Triveda Capital raises Rs 80 crore in first round of realty fund
news.para: The maiden fund targets an asset under management of $1 billion over the next five years. Of the total fund size, Century Real Estate Holdings' family office has committed 15%.

news.title: Golden Growth Fund to raise Rs 400 crore to buy land in South Delhi
news.para: Golden Growth Fund has closed the first round of fundraising and also acquired a land parcel in South Delhi's upscale Anand Niketan residential colony.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP directs Ireo Victory Valley RWA to allow EWS families access to flats
news.para: In a recent grievance hearing, chaired by deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav, the allottees of EWS flats accused the RWA of not allowing them to live in their own properties and denying them basic amenities available to other residents of the society, such as access to parks and other common areas.

news.title: JSW Cement files draft papers with Sebi to raise Rs 4,000 crore via IPO
news.para: As a part of the OFS, AP Asia Opportunistic Holdings Pte Ltd and Synergy Metals Investments Holding Ltd will offload shares worth Rs 937.5 crore each, and State Bank of India (SBI) will divest shares valued at Rs 125 crore.

news.title: China Evergrande onshore unit's administrator seeks details from creditors ahead of November 14 meeting
news.para: The Guangzhou Intermediate People's Court ruled last week that Evergrande unit Guangzhou Kailong Real Estate enter into bankruptcy and liquidation proceedings and appointed a liquidation group as the company's administrator, according to a court filing.

news.title: Ajmera Realty appoints Jayesh Mehta as independent director
news.para: Mehta, who previously served as managing director and country treasurer at Bank of America N.A., has over 35 years of experience in the Indian fixed-income markets.

news.title: Sweden's EQT to acquire PropertyGuru in $1.1 billion deal
news.para: As part of the deal, PropertyGuru's shareholders will receive $6.70 apiece, a 7% premium to the firm's last close on Thursday.

news.title: Delhi-NCR's real estate market received PE investment worth $633.3 million in H1 2024: Report
news.para: Out of the total investment in Delhi-NCR, office assets received USD 483.6 million, while residential USD 149.6 million.

news.title: Untangling the delays: The impact of Delhi master plan 2041 notification hold-ups
news.para: The delay is not only disappointing but also causing significant confusion among key players, including private sector companies, institutional investors, HNI family offices and landowners. The uncertainty surrounding the formalization of MPD2041 is leading to a standstill in critical urban development initiatives.

news.title: Home prices in Seoul rise at fastest pace in more than four years
news.para: The house transaction price index rose 0.15% in July, faster than a monthly rise of 0.04% in June and the fastest since October 2023, according to the Korea Real Estate Board.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth Rs 678 crore of Avantha Group in PMLA case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate attached properties worth over Rs 678 crore belonging to the Avantha Group, owned by Gautam Thapar, in connection with an alleged bank fraud and money-laundering case. The investigation revealed that Avantha Group companies diverted Rs 1,307 crore out of loans obtained from a consortium of banks led by SBI.

news.title: Karnataka 'temporarily' bans land use change in Western Ghats
news.para: The Karnataka government proposed a master plan to protect the ecologically sensitive Western Ghats by temporarily banning any change in land usage patterns while maintaining existing villages and towns. Forest Minister Eshwar Khandre cited natural calamities to emphasize the urgency, aiming to balance biodiversity protection with residents' livelihoods without evicting populations.

news.title: Bombay HC directs Mhada to issue NOC for BMC to issue OC to Mahim building
news.para: Justices Mahesh Sonak and Kamal Khata on Aug 13 directed Mhada’s CEO “to inquire into the entire episode and conduct of officers responsible which resulted in loss to Mhada/public exchequer”.

news.title: SBI-led banks key to insolvency case against Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: Updated claims as of end July show that financial creditors including homebuyers are owed a total of Rs 51,510 crore led by SBI which with close to Rs 15,500 crore is the largest creditor with 30% of the debt followed by ICICI Bank with 18% and IDBI Bank with 11%.
